<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>FRONT NON-DRIVE STEERING AXLE: ROCKWELL - LUBRICATION AND MAINTENANCE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec id="hl0200507">
        <title>LUBRICATION AND MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>For lubrication intervals and type of lubricant, refer to GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000
                Master Service Manual.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>KING PINS - SEALED AND EASY STEER&#8482; FRONT AXLES</title>
            <para>On sealed and Easy Steer&#8482; front axles, the grease fittings are on the top and bottom king pin
                caps of the knuckle.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the tires touch the ground.
                    <emph type="bold">Do not raise the vehicle</emph>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate the king pins through the grease fittings on the top and bottom of the knuckle
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0200543">Figure 43</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0200543" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g0200543" filename="../figg02/G0200543.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 43. Lubricate King Pins</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Apply lubricant until new lubricant comes from the thrust bearing seal and the upper
                    shim pack.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
